messages.content:
**ANNOUNCEMENT**

G’day @everyone

So we have some exciting news – we can now announce that a business will be utilising the MeowCoin blockchain.

Primeur is an Australian start up by wine professionals looking to evolve the category and disrupt existing players. It is offering Australian wineries a never-before-realised opportunity to pre-sell their product each vintage. This pre-sale will take away some of the financial burden wineries encounter when producing their premium offering as wine lovers can purchase prior to bottling their favourite wines without fear that they will miss out on a vintage or be scalped for price by retailers. These sales can be made at increased margins since they remove the middle-man of retailers.

Blockchain technology allows Primeur to to issue a certificate of providence (which in wine is very important as 20% of wine sold around the world is fraudulent) and allow them to be traded prior to bottling. Once the required age for the wine is reached, bottling will take place and the wines sent to owners of the NFT through a secure and private interaction. At that point, the NFT will be marked as delivered (aka burnt) although the certificate of providence will remain on the blockchain for posterity and reference.

Primeur are partnering with existing software company https://www.withwine.com/ to engage with the existing wineries on their software platform and offer them the chance to utilise pre-sale of their premium wines through Primeur.

More information will be released on this project as time goes on, but we’re excited to bring this project to your attention. Development for integration of their tokenising of wine is underway and is planned to be completed by December. 

https://www.primeur.vin/

messages.content:
Hello @everyone 

We can happily announce that **Dex-TRADE are now accepting deposits for Meowcoin**. 🥳 

To ensure complete understanding, we wanted to advise that the user interface for Dex-TRADE does not show confirmations of coins that are incoming. What does this mean?

When you transfer coins to Dex-TRADE, the Block Explorer will show you how many confirmations have been completed until your deposit arrives, not Dex-TRADE. 

So, as you send funds, take your Txid and put it into the block explorer and **wait for 320 confirmations**. Once 320 confirmations are completed, your MEWC will appear on Dex-TRADE. I've attached a screenshot of what I watched last night (I wanted to test before announcing to ensure everything worked - for transparency's sake I moved 1000 MEWC across).

I know this is going to catch some people out so we wanted to make special note of it. Please feel free to ask us any Q's in #🐈cat-chat .

@Ghost089 and his team have been brilliant in helping set up our very own NFT marketplace. This will have some fantastic artists put up their work as well as @Melchizedek sell a limited edition, 100 run NFT set utilising the Calico cat (our beloved emblem). 

Additionally, we're keen to sell some limited edition merchandise. I have a few things lined up for this - will keep you informed!

I’d also like to call out and request any budding artists to DM me; I have an idea for a great set I’d like to make live. Artist will keep all the proceeds, of course, but commissioning work is something I’ve always wanted to do and there will be a little ‘bonus’ in there for you 😉

**3. Layer 2**

There are now works in play for Layer 2 options to come to Meowcoin. As discussed, Primeur.vin is looking to build on Meowcoin and with it, a group called the https://www.helixcollective.com/ are interested in building out both that solution and a number of others. I can’t mention too much more but we’re excited by where this will take us. 

**4. P2B IEO**

As you all know, P2B put an IEO out for us at 1c, which is incredibly exciting. We’re grateful for their listing of us and we look forward to being able to trade on their exchange once the IEO has completed. 

**5. Zelcore**

There’s been some delays with Zelcore integration due to their own roadmap issues. We’re empathetic to this and will continue to work with them to get Meowcoin loaded into their great software.

**6. Decentralised Blog**

One of the talented developers in our community has offered to build me a decentralised blog. This will be a blueprint for a future service we’re keen to offer whereby each blog post and entry will be logged on the blockchain for the purpose of identifying authorial ownership. 

If we get it up and running, I’m hoping we can then make an adjustment to get it on a Flux docker and loaded into their dApp ecosystem. This will see our first fully decentralised dApp built for the Meowcoin ecosystem with purpose and meaning. The blogging software will be clean, ad free and at complete control of the owner - just the way it should be. 

**7. Pawprint**

With work on Empawrium nearing completion, we’re in the process of looking into Pawprint - the animal adoption software built for shelters to tokenise pets. Work to scope this out is beginning and we hope to achieve its completion in our roadmap timing. 

Any further Q’s, please feel free to ask me in #🐈cat-chat !
